-- Turkey’s Halkbank Begins Work on Creating Own Credit Card Brand
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-04-11T06:44:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/turkey-s-halkbank-begins-work-on-creating-own-credit-card-brand.html
Turkiye Halk Bankasi AS, a state-
run Turkish bank, said it was beginning work on its own credit
card brand.  The bank’s board of directors approved a plan to begin work
on creating a new Halkbank credit card brand, Halkbank said in a
statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market close
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
